\@writefile{lof}{\contentsline {figure}{\numberline {2}{\ignorespaces Agent Bazaar system diagram. \textbf  {Lane 1 (Environment)}: The market state $s_t$ is observed by agents subject to a token budget $\tau $ (Search Friction), agents emit actions, and the environment performs market clearing to produce $s_{t+1}$. \textbf  {Lane 2 (Agent Internals)}: Each agent is an LLM backbone (one of five model families) prompted with a structured CoT template; actions are parsed from JSON output. The Skeptical Guardian applies forensic analysis before acting. \textbf  {Lane 3 (Sybil Structure)}: A single Deceptive Principal coordinates $K$ seller identities via a shared signal. Identities with reputation below threshold are retired and replaced, resetting the trust signal available to buyers.}}{5}{figure.2}\protected@file@percent }
\newlabel{fig:methodology}{{2}{5}{Agent Bazaar system diagram. \textbf {Lane 1 (Environment)}: The market state $s_t$ is observed by agents subject to a token budget $\tau $ (Search Friction), agents emit actions, and the environment performs market clearing to produce $s_{t+1}$. \textbf {Lane 2 (Agent Internals)}: Each agent is an LLM backbone (one of five model families) prompted with a structured CoT template; actions are parsed from JSON output. The Skeptical Guardian applies forensic analysis before acting. \textbf {Lane 3 (Sybil Structure)}: A single Deceptive Principal coordinates $K$ seller identities via a shared signal. Identities with reputation below threshold are retired and replaced, resetting the trust signal available to buyers}{figure.2}{}}
